Defintion: Petals do not exceed the length of the inner and outer sepals.
Petals exceed the length of the inner and outer sepals.
Opening and separation of the petals. At least one petal is free from touching adjacent petals. Outer sepals begin to abscise. Nectar is visibly collecting in spurs.
Initiated by partial anther dehiscence, followed by complete dehiscence,  and finally flower abscisson
